====Usage notes====
In Old Chinese, sons of a same father are referred to in order as {{zh-l|伯|first}}, {{zh-l|仲|second}}, {{zh-l|叔|third}} and {{zh-l|季 |fourth}}. The usage of {{zh-l|*仲}} and {{zh-l|*季}} was later eliminated but {{zh-l|*伯}} and {{zh-l|*叔}} remained in use when referring to one's father's elder and younger brothers and male cousins. Moreover, {{lang|zh|伯仲叔季}} were commonly used in personal names in the past, and this is still occasionally seen nowadays.

